==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Classical Greek ''glauk&#333;ma'', literally "an opacity of the crystalline lens", derived from ''glaukós'' "gray, silvery"

===Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''glaucoma'''

#An eye disease or disorder that is defined as a characteristic optic neuropathy, or disease of the optic nerve, possibly, if untreated, leading to damage of the optic disc of the retina and resultant visual field loss, which can lead to blindness.

